    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1875-05-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1875-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="311" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d311">
                <head>No. 603.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cushing</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-05-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 13, 1875</date>.
                                (Received June 1.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 382.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the satisfaction to report that the
                            final payment on account of the “Virginius,” received by me on the 5th,
                            as previously reported, has this day been remitted by me to London, by
                            eight-day bills of Messrs. Bayo &amp; Co. on Messrs. Murrieta &amp; Go.,
                            and that thus the Spanish government, without availing itself of the six
                            months’ time stipulated in the agreement of March 11, has voluntarily
                            discharged its entire obligation in two months, for the purpose of
                            showing its good faith and its good-will toward the United States.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C. CUSHING.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
